<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Linse on 04-25-2001 06:25 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">It's not a cheat in my opinion. This is an exploit of the game. There is a difference. lemme  see if i can explain it another way with other games;

Back in the day of quake1, and 2 someone figured out that if you shoot a rocket at your feet at the highest part of your jump you would get some extra height at the cost of some health. It wasn't a script or file, but an exploit of the game's physics. Everyone could do it. And certain maps had power-ups that could only be gotten to if you used this jump method. It gives you an advantage as a player against others who don't use it, but only if you choice not to learn it. I lost a Q2 tournament back in the day, against someone who did this while i never knew about it. I NEVER once thought he was cheating.  
Same goes for the strafe jumping. A new exploit in half-life's game engine where people use a strafe jump technique to "bunny-hop" (counter-strike is a good example) in order to get to places faster than just plain running. It wasn't anything but the skill of the player (trust me, it's not an easy feat to do, and if you can do it, more power to ya) who was able to do this type of jumping.

My final example is more of a real life encounter. Some teachers in high school let us use 1 index card to put notes on for a test. We were allowed to use the card during the test and whatever you wanted to write on it was fine, one sided only. Now i can write REALLY small and i could get more notes on it then most people. Would that make me a cheater? Just becuase i'm exploiting a talent i have for writing small? Should i just learn to write the average size of everyone else just to be fair?  I think not.

Look if it's in the game, and everyone can do it (not if you should do it, but if you can) then it's not really a cheat. If you had a lvl 60 character you would twink your newbie character (most of you would) whether it's equipment or some plat. That's not cheating but taking advantage of what you have.

Just my opinion,  flame on........</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
